Title: Discrete Structures
Meeting Date: Meeting Date: May 04, 2020 to Aug 14, 2020 Days: Mon Time: 17:35 - 20:25
Other: Section Information:Virtual attendance at the days/times listed is required. Expect 9 hours commitment per week (on average). 4 hours at the described mandatory dates and times, plus 5 hours independent work. Lectures and tutorials will be online, up to 4 hours of material each week (lectures 3 hours, tutorial lessons and online activity / quiz up to 1 hour).  1-2 hours independent review each week. Assignments will be done using a suitable document editor (Word, Latex) and are expected to require about 3-4 hours each week (averaged over the semester). Office hours will be online. You will need access to a computer with a sufficient internet connection to meet these time/resource requirements for the course. Precludes additional credit for MATH 1800 and 1805. NOTE: As of Fall 2017, grade of C- or above required in order to take COMP 2804.

Title: Intensive Game Dev. Project
Meeting Date: Meeting Date: May 04, 2020 to Aug 14, 2020 Days: Tue Thu Time: 18:05 - 20:55
Also Register In: Section Information:Adv Topics in CS- Intensive Game Development Project Virtual attendance at the day/times listed is required. This course involves using an existing game engine to develop a complete game from a high-level design. Student will cooperate in a small group to design the architecture of the system and construct the algorithms and software to realize a polished, playable game. Admission is by permission of the School, please submit a registration override request.  For BCS students only with priority to 3rd and 4th year students. Prerequisites: COMP2401, COMP 2402 and COMP2404.
